{"title": "Permissive callback disable configuration", "summary": " When using except for disabling a callback, there is a high chance of skipping important access control logic by accident.  ### Remediations  \u2705 Prefer enumerating all of the actions using `only`:  ```ruby skip_before_action :access_control, only: %i[public_action1 public_action2] ``` ", "description": "\nWhen using except for disabling a callback, there is a high chance\nof skipping important access control logic by accident.\n\n### Remediations\n\n\u2705 Prefer enumerating all of the actions using `only`:\n\n```ruby\nskip_before_action :access_control, only: %i[public_action1 public_action2]\n```\n", "recommendations": "", "taxonomy": ["CWE-284"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/ruby_rails_insecure_disabling_of_callback"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}